wines.alcohol: The Bengal tiger lives in the Indian subcontinent. It is listed as endangered species since 2008 and there are only about 2,500 individuals left. Most live in India, but there are a few hundered also in Bangladesh, Nepal and Bhutan. The species is threatened by poaching and loss of habitat caused by climat change. The Bengal tiger is one of the biggest wild cats alive and is the national animal of India and Bangladesh.
